    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1850-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1850-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="222" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <head>
                    <seg type="margin">[668]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Clayton</persName>, Secretary of State, to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Hall</persName>, district
                                attorney.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                        State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1850-05-26">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 26,
                                1850</date>.</dateline>
                <p>Your several notes of yesterday’s date were received to-day. In reply
                                to that part of your note dated yesterday, at 3½ p.m., I am directed
                                to state that you have full authority from the President to act
                                under the eighth section of the act of 20th April, 1818, in order to
                                seize and detain munitions of war intended to be used in aid of the
                                Cuban expedition. It is expected by the President that you will, as
                                far as in your power, strictly execute the law.</p>
            </div>
